==English==

{{rank|laws|run|position|541|copy|opened|purpose|fall}}

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[copie]]'', {{ML.}} ''[[copia]]'' "reproduction, transcript," from {{L.}} ''[[copia]]'' "plenty, means".  It should be noted here of the possible relation of the modern '''copy''' to the hebrew [[כף]] '''caph'''.   Although '''kaph''' means literally "cup", the '''kaph''' is also a hebrew letter that acts as a prepositional modifier meaning, appropriately, '''like or similar to'''.  

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|cop|y}}

# The result of copying (''confer'' [[original]]); an identical duplication.
#: ''Please bring me the '''copies''' of those reports.''
# An imitation of inferior quality.
#: ''That handbag is a '''copy'''.  You can tell because the buckle is different.''
# (''journalism'') The text that is to be typeset.
# {{uncountable}} The text of newspaper articles.
#: ''Submit all '''copy''' to the appropriate editor.''

